cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.LG

The paper discusses the accuracy of different citation-based taxonomies of scientific and technical knowledge, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.LG). The use of direct citation, bibliographic coupling, and co-citation also suggests a focus on network analysis (cs.SI) and computational complexity (cs.CY). Finally, the use of journal schema as a comparison suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL).
